getColumns(String, String, String, String) - Method in class com.thereisnogravity.jdbcstub.DatabaseMetaDataStub
This is a metadata query which returns the columns in a named table.
Each record includes the following columns:
TABLE_CAT String => table catalog, set to the output of DatabaseMetaDataStub.getCatalogTerm() TABLE_SCHEM String => table schema, set to the output of DatabaseMetaDataStub.getSchemaName() TABLE_NAME String => table name COLUMN_NAME String => column name DATA_TYPE int => SQL type from java.sql.Types, and we are always making a VARCHAR TYPE_NAME String => Data source dependent type name, which is always VARCHAR COLUMN_SIZE int => column size (fixed at 80) There are supposed to be more metadata columns, but we are just ignoring those
